Aroma/Taste: Toffee, berries, fruits
Appearance: Very simple. A bit of head but not outrageous
Palate: Excellent. Fairly strong flavor but still went down easy.
Overall: One of the better bocks Ive tried. Im becoming a fan of Anchor

Aroma and taste: of licorice, smoke and other strong malts and molasses. Very sweet. 
Palate: Pinched the nerves in my mouth and almost ripped my tongue off.
Overall: Fun to sample, but not a full glass. Too much alcohol. 1 small shot was the most any of us could handle, and we can handle a lot.

beer_brewer_name: Brouwerij der Trappistenabdij De Achelse Kluis
review_blob:
One taste and this was instantly my current favorite beer. I love Trappists and this one beats them all (never tried the Wes...velten sp?).

The dry fruity aroma sucks you in then you take a taste. It starts sweet and lightly fruity and just the tiniest hint of licorice, then warms with a bit of sherry and 9.5 abv up on its way down. Finally, after a few seconds, you get the very mild hop bitterness to perfectly counter all the maltiness.

Mouthfeel is exactly what you expect from a Belgian Trappist. Bubbly and long.
